text.tspan: URLium 1.0.3
By ElectricShmoo
Featuring: "Ugetblock Command"
RCON/OP "/ugetblock x y z" command to query block data remotely for external scripting.
Featuring: "/webcom Command"
Any user may transmit a message to the webserver with a custom command.
The actual name of the command is "webcom" by default, but can be configured to anything.
Command name is config value is set as:
messageCommand=webcom
The POST message sent to the server includes the username, timestamp, and message:
{ "message":"This is some text to send to the server :)", "device":"message",
"user":"ElectricShmoo", "ts" : "1692518860884" }
Things to consider when writing a server-side receiver for these messages:
- Consider the implications of the received message (filter for authority if necessary).
- Avoid implementing anything too dangerous in the webserver's response.
- If using 3rd-party or A.I. APIs, consider the implications of data collection.
- Consider the security of your webserver-mcserver connection and USE A FIREWALL!!
command: /ugetblock -37 71 -130
returns: minecraft:grass_block[snowy=false]
... minecraft:log[axis=x]
... minecraft:jungle_stairs[facing=west,half=bottom,shape=straight....
minecraft:chest[facing=east,type=single,waterlogged=false]
{Items:[{Count:1b,Slot:0b,id:"minecraft:dirt"}]}
